Tradeoffs between Compression Algs
	gzip: 
		earlier 
		fastest
		widely available
	bzip2:
		smaller archives
		Not as widely available as gzip
	xz:
		newer
		Best compression ratio
		
Example: Create a compressed archive of the /etc directory
	tar -czf /root/etcbackup.tar.gz /etc
	
Listing a Compressed Archive

	There is no need to specify compression alg because that is stored in the archive's header

